"{\"uid\": \"dakotanewsnow.com-2024-08-21-special-olympics-host-heroes-pull-sunday\", \"text\": \"SIOUX FALLS, S.D. (Dakota News Now) - Special Olympics South Dakota will host their annual Heroes Pull in Sioux Falls on August 25.  Teams of up to 10 will get the chance to pull a Sioux Falls firetruck and a SWAT BearCat.  Teams will compete to see who can pull the firetruck 40 feet in the fastest amount of time.  For teams that cannot fill all 10 roster spots, Special Olympic athletes will be on standby to help.  The event will take place from 4 to 6 p.m. at the Unify Center.  Organizer Nancy Lehner and Special Olympic athletes Derek Smith and Lydia Van Stedum stopped by Dakota News Now to share more about the event.  View more details on the Heroes Pullhere.  Copyright 2024 Dakota News Now. All rights reserved.\"}"